Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. While it comes to the boil, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1%400g can} in a #colander{}.

When the water is boiling, add @salt{0.25%tsp}, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan.

> Leave to cook for 10 mins, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a saucepan on medium-high heat. Once the oil is hot, add the onion and season with @salt and @pepper. Cook until the onion is soft, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Add the garlic, @chipotle paste{20%g} and @Mexican spice{1}, stir and cook for ~{1%minute}.

> Use less chipotle paste and spice if you don't like heat.

Pour in the @water{300%ml}, stir in the @vegetable stock powder{1}, @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g} and add the @red split lentils{100%g}. Stir together, bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium, cover with a lid and simmer until the lentils are tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Stir every few mins to ensure the lentils aren't sticking to the bottom of the pan. Add the kidney beans for the final ~{5%minutes}, and a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

While the rice and chilli cooks, grate the @lime{1}(zested) and halve the lime. Quarter the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} and finely chop the @coriander{1}(finely chopped) (stalks and all). Squeeze half the lime juice into a #bowl{} and add the @olive oil{1%tbsp}, season with @salt and @pepper. Stir together, then add the tomatoes and coriander. Mix together and keep to one side.

Once cooked, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir in the lime zest. Spoon into #bowls{}, top with the lentil chilli and finish with the tomato and coriander salsa and a dollop of @soured cream{75%g}. Cut the remaining lime into wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!